            <mi>e</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>t</mi>
      </mrow>
    </mfenced>
  </math>, by equation <a href="#x1-9008r3">3</a>, and it is associated with a slowdown of biological activity (sleep, for example), whereas the negative values are associated to a faster pace (wake for example).
</p>
<p class="indent">
  As a fundamental feature of the model that we will analyze next, we assume that the speed of rotation with respect to the compacified time is constant, which leads to a radius
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
