<p class="indent">
  This assumption “geometrizes” time even further: acceleration and slow-down will be <span class="cmti-10">seen </span>as contraction and enlargement of a cylinder in §<a href="#x1-170004e4e2">4.4.2</a>. In
  that section, as an application, we will develop a geometrical analysis of biological rate variability, and, as an example, we will consider heart rate. Note that this radius
  
  <math display="inline" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
    <msub>
      <mrow>
