<p class="indent">
  This case analysis has an actual correspondence with empirical data for the first two cases (see for example Hellbrugge et al. <a id="pagee18" href="#X0-hellbrugge1964circadian">1964</a>;
  Cranford <a href="#X0-cranford1983body">1983</a>). We believe that theoretically biological time should be always cofluent so that the third case should never be realized. Indeed, the existing data,
